name: Target
directions: It's right by the entrance.

name: 122 South Main Street building
directions: There are two unisex bathrooms in the basement floor of this building.

name: Sidetrack Bar & Grill
directions: This bathroom might be difficult to get to/find unless you are seated by it, because it is tucked away in one of the side rooms and this place is huge!

name: The Ugly Mug
directions: There is a locking single stall bathroom in the side area with the counter/bar stools by the front window
comment: you may have to ask for the bathroom key or it may be sitting out on a table

name: Espresso Royale
directions: Keys are available at the counter (you can just grab them), there are two single stall gendered bathrooms. they are in plain view but they do lock.
comment: keys are at the counter but you don't have to ask

name: lab (coffee shop)
directions: there is a key with a metal scoop by the front door and the bathroom is in the back
comment: for paying customers

name: Hoby's Market
directions: Very back of the store, between the meat department and the dairy section

name: University of Michigan University Health Service
directions: First floor to the left of the front door

name: University of Michigan Medical Science I (MSI)
directions: 3rd floor, near the connecting hallway between MSI and MSII.
comment: Open to anyone with building access. Locking door opens to a hallway with a second door, one stall inside.

name: University of Michigan Biomedical Sciences Research Building (BSRB)
directions: Ground floor, to the right of the cafe area. There are multi-stall gendered restrooms, drinking fountains, and on the right side there is one unisex/gender neutral bathroom.
comment: Can be used by anyone during open building hours.

name: Freehand Chicago Hotel/Hostel
directions:
Head through lobby past elevators through lounge area and up stairs. Immediately to your left against the wall, before curtain leading to bar. Wheelchair lift is here too.  No ramp though.

Alternatively, head through lobby to elevators, you'll see stairs going down (with restrooms painted on the wall). Follow signs to bathrooms. There are two large washrooms with stalls but signing is gender neutral.
comment: They run a lot of events in evenings in the lounge space so that may be better during the day. Downstairs will be a better option then. No hotel key required and events mean people are alerts coming and going.

name: University of Michigan Palmer Commons
directions: In the sitting area next to the cafe, next to the printers. Single unisex restroom with lock.
comment: Can be used by anyone during open hours.

name: Mighty Good Coffee
directions: in the back (on the espresso bar side) there is a single stall unisex restroom
comment: presumably for paying customers

name: Cathy's Deli
directions: Back of restaurant. Black doors
comment: Super nice staff. No one will hassle you.

name: TACO-ma Yucatan Cicken
directions: just to the left of the counter
comment: probably customers-only, but I forgot to ask (good soup!)

name: Bay Street Biergarten
directions: Single stall, past men's and women's rooms

name: Inova Fairfax Hospital
directions: Every patient' room has its own bathroom and every unit has 1-2 single stalls for all. They also have women/men stalls on lower level.

name: Frita Batidos
directions: Straight back
comment: 2 identical single stall restrooms. no gender specificity.

name: The Detroit Bubble Tea Company
directions: In the middle by the area you wait for your order/in the sitting area.
comment: For paying customers.

name: Bombay Heights
directions: Back of the restaurant
comment: You must be a paying customer

name: California State University, Northridge, Arbor Grill
directions: Sort of hidden, outside, on the library side of Freudian Sip.

name: London Drugs
directions: At the back of the store, to the left of the pharmacy.

name: Johnny's Gone FIshing
directions: Toward the back near the stack of dishes (only bathroom)

name: St. Andrew's United Methodist Church
directions: In the front door and to the left off of the narthex, through the coat room.

name: Jimmy John's
directions: In the back of the store, just past the pop machine
comment: Don't need to be a paying customer. The bathrooms are "gendered" but there's no actual differences between the two and the staff lets anyone use whichever bathroom they prefer. They're single person bathrooms

name: TDS
directions: In between the bus stop zones.

name: Garden Grill
directions: Gender neutral bathroom in the back of the restaurant, back of the outdoor patio.

name: Champlain College
directions:
Third floor- enter from Rozendaal Ctyd, take a left 

Second floor- enter from Street side glass staircase to second floor, take second left, take second right, go past blond wood double doors, it's on your left.
comment: Meant for students staff and faculty, but if you say you're here for the art exhibit if anyone asks, no one will bother you.

name: Coffee XChange
comment: Used to be two gendered single stall restrooms; after remodel is one single stall unisex one.

name: Coffee XChange
comment: Used to be two gendered single stall restrooms; after remodel is one single stall unisex one.

name: The Station Theatre
directions: west side of the building, opposite of the lobby
comment: There are two single user bathrooms, one big enough for a person with a wheelchair. When you pay for your ticket, you can ask the person at the box office where the bathroom is.

name: H2O Salon
directions: It's at the back of the salon, down the hall. Ask a staff member for a key.
comment: You probably have to be a paying customer, but the salon owner and staff are great. If you're bold, ask if you can use the bathroom and explain why.

name: Third Unitarian Church
directions: Go in the gated entrance, past the table (to the left) and through the doorway to the back of the green room
comment: Only open to the public on Sunday morning. There is one accessible and several non-accessible single stall unisex restrooms.

name: Johnnys Gone Fishing
directions: Straight toward the back on the left. They are gendered single stall restrooms, but the workers are very low key and don't really care

name: Memphis Gay and Lesbian Community Center
SOAS School of Oriental and African studies
directions: Basement of main building
comment: Accessible as a student, member of staff or with a visitor's badge

name: Muffin Break
directions: At the back of the shop
comment: Also includes baby changing facilities

name: Linda's Bar & Grill
comment: Linda's ordered gender-neutral bathroom signs immediately after HB2's passage and posted about it on social media: https://www.facebook.com/LindasBarandGrill/photos/a.216373845045559.68472.119225111427100/1307145099301756/?type=3&theater. Not sure if the bathrooms are wheelchair accessible though.

name: Splash Designz
comment: we are open M-F 8:30 am - 5:00 pm. Simply ask and you may use our restroom

name: The Candy Factory
directions: In the back corner on the first floor.
comment: Generally for employees and clients, but would be a safe place for anyone who asked.

name: Northern Arizona University, University Union Fieldhouse
directions: Right back corner of lobby behind the stairs.
comment: Open to staff, students and guests during business hours. There are three single stall bathrooms with toilet and sink. One of them has a shower stall.

name: Northern Arizona University, University Union
directions:
First floor, across from LEADS Center.
In Starbucks, back hallway.
comment: Open to staff, students and guests during business hours. Both have two single stall bathrooms with toilet and sink.

name: Northern Arizona University, Student & Academic Services Building
directions:
First floor, right of elevators (beyond admissions).
Third floor, right of elevators.
comment:
First floor, right of elevators is open to staff, students and guests during business hours. Has a toilet and sink.
Third floor, right of elevators is signed as "shower." Has toilet, sink and shower.

name: Northern Arizona University, Skydome
street: 1701 S. San Francisco St., Flagstaff, AZ, 86011
directions: By the main entrance as you enter the Skydome.
comment: Open to staff, students and guests during business hours. Has a toilet, sink and baby changing station.

name: Northern Arizona University, Science and Health Building
directions: Passed the elevators.
comment: Open to staff, students and guests during business hours. Has a single stall toilet and sink.

name: Northern Arizona University, North Hall
directions: First floor, left of north entrance. Also, first floor, west wing hallway.
comment: Open to staff, students and guests during business hours. Restroom that is first floor, left of north entrance has a toilet, urinal and sink (this one is not handicap accessible). Restroom that is first floor, west wing hallway has a toilet and sink (this one is handicap accessible).

name: Northern Arizona University, Native American Cultural Center
directions: Left of front entrance.
comment: Open to staff, students, and guests during business hours. Has a toilet, sink, and baby changing station.

name: Northern Arizona University, Liberal Arts Building
street: S. San Francisco St, Flagstaff, AZ 86001
directions: Family restroom, next to room 120.
comment: Open to staff, students and guests during business hours. Has a toilet and sink.

name: Northern Arizona University, Institute for Human Development
directions: Next to room 123.
comment: Open to staff, students, and guests during business hours. Has a toilet and sink.

name: Northern Arizona University, Gammage
directions: Main floor, opposite of room 106. Also, main floor next to room 107.
comment: Open to staff, students and guests during business hours. Opposite of room 106 has a toilet and sink. Next to room 107 has a toilet, sink, and baby changing station.

name: Northern Arizona University, College of Business
directions: Next to room 3006, by gendered restrooms. Also next to room 4006, by gendered restrooms.
comment: Just a toilet and sink for both. Available to staff, students and guests during business hours.

name: The Pinhook
directions: Two bathrooms that are both "gender neutral milk hotel."
comment: Very LGBT friendly performance space.

name: UNC Rosenau Hall
directions: Between Rosenau, McGavran-Greenberg and Michael Hooker Research Center, across from 235 Rosenau.
comment: Formerly women's restroom with two stalls, now has lock to be all-gender individual-use bathroom. Sign not up yet. I don't think it's wheelchair accessible.

name: the Petition
directions: The entrance area splits into three. Go down the centre hallway. It should probably be the third on the left.
comment: You might be able to just walk on through because you don't pass by a cashier very closely. Otherwise you can get a kind of overpriced drink?

name: Flinders Square
directions: It's in the hallway to the right of the Coles (when you're facing the Coles), right at the end after the gendered bathrooms.
comment: You don't need to pay anything. It's just a public bathroom. It's open as long as the grocery store is (and probably a bit longer)

name: The Center on High
directions: First floor, all the way to the back on the right.
comment: Open to the public. Can only be used by one person at a time.

name: Hammered Lamb
directions: Inside to the back
comment: You may or may not have to be 21 to get in, only been once

name: Soma Massage Therapy
directions: Access Soma Massage Therapy by using the back door to the building.
comment: Please feel free to use our restroom free of charge, 7 days a week.  You are welcome and safe here.

name: Fine Arts Center
directions: 2 sets of All Gender Restrooms on 2nd floor of Theater side of FAC. Multi stall, one has urinal.

name: Target
directions: Right by the front entrance doors

name: OSO Restaurant
directions: In the back to the right of the patio, you have to be eating or drinking though.
comment: Staff is nice and food is awesome. Two unisex single restrooms, so rarely a wait.

name: Genesee Health System
directions: If you walk in it will be straight back, then on the left.
comment: This is a medical health service center, the check-in or security officer may ask, but if you say you just stopped in for the restroom, I don't think there will be a problem.

name: Thirsty Lion Pub & Grill
comment: You Have to be a paying customer.

name: Thirsty Lion Pub & Grill
comment: You Have to be a paying customer.

name: Target
directions: Right when you walk in, hang a right past the sports clothes

name: Thirsty Lion Pub  & Grill
comment: You have to be a paying customer.

name: Thirsty Lion Pub  & Grill
comment: You have to be a paying customer.

name: 67 Biltmore Eatery
comment: Owners Emily and Adam are awsome!

name: Allegheny College Campus Center
directions: They are in Doane Hall on the first floor. Head to the right from the main door.

name: Family Care Center
comment: posting on behalf of the owners

name: Massage Envy Falls Pointe
directions: Through the hall past the treatment rooms, back door and then to the left.
comment: Generally for client use but just ask front desk staff.

name: Fallout
directions: Unisex bathroom is handicap accessible and in the back room
comment: This is a bar so 18+, it is closed to the public Friday-Sunday.

name: Tried and True Tattoo
directions: Up two flights of stairs but we also have an elevator. Free parking in the back.
comment: I am a trans person who is the body piercer at Tried and True Tattoo. This is terrible. Come pee in peace.

name: Starbucks
directions: Just to the right as you enter the front door.

name: c.s. Rey Heredia
comment: This is an occupied anarchist social centre where people are in touch and friendly with trans community. You can enter and use any bathroom with no questions

name: Renfe train station
comment: People can stare at you ir seem confused but there is no agressive manners usually

name: UNC Thurston Arthritis Research Center
directions: 1st floor near entryway by pedestrian bridge. Behind Alpine cafe, head back toward elevators.
comment: Open during business hours, need keycard after hours. Single stall. It's also family style & large space of you have a kid.

name: Poor Richard's
directions: For all businesses in their block. So, Rico's, Little Richards, the restaurant and the book store. All their bathrooms are in the back
comment: Just walk on in. :) Awesome people.

name: Starbucks
directions: Back of the cafe, right next to back door.

name: Slifka center for Jewish life at Yale
directions: Floor where you come in, walk straight back and turn left. It's on the little walkway that looks over the dining hall.
comment: Usually open during the day and nobody will question your right to be there

name: Blue State Coffee
directions: Go back and left, it's kind of across as far left as you can go.
comment: Probably you're supposed to be a paying customer

name: Linsly-Chittenden Hall
directions: Near the high street entrance in an alcove
comment: Open during the day and you can def just walk in

name: Columbia Metropolitan Airport
directions: Family/ single restroom on Ticketing level. On the Left when approaching TSA check. I don't think there are any family/ single restrooms once past security or on the baggage level.

name: 81 Wall, Yale
directions: Single stall gender neutral bathrooms on every floor

name: California Dreaming
directions: Two single-person restrooms near lower- level earing area. Located on the right when walking toward the kitchen.
comment: Customer.s.

name: Calhoun College
directions: Down the stairs from the common room, turn left at the bottom and at the end of the hall with the other bathrooms.
comment: Can get in during the day

name: UNC School of Dentistry Koury Oral Health Sciences Bldg
directions: Ground floor down hallway by the stairs. Two gender neutral bathrooms.

name: Silliman College
directions: Third floor, through doors on the right towards computer room.
comment: Open to anyone during the day

name: Coa Mexican eatery
directions: In the back past the kitchen
comment: The food is so yummy also!!
